---
description: Parser quality rules for Git output
globs: ["src-tauri/src/**/*.rs"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Git parsers are critical infrastructure and must be robust.

Rules:
- parsers should be pure where possible
- test parsers with realistic fixtures
- handle malformed or partial input gracefully
- do not assume happy-path only
- prefer explicit parsing over fragile string hacks
- isolate parsing logic from command execution

Parser expectations:
- status parser distinguishes staged, unstaged, untracked, conflicted
- diff parser handles binary changes and renames
- log parser handles merge commits and multiple parents
- branch parser handles current branch, upstream, ahead/behind when available

Do not:
- bury parsing rules in UI or command handler code
- silently discard records without intent